Project requirements

I believe I expressed my creativity through making the meme and gif by creating my own template and using functions such as image_noise() and image_modulation(). And creating a gif using frames from a captivating scene and using image_animate() to bring it together



Part A

Part A had us creating a github account and repository, I had already made a github account but had never made a repository before. In this new repository we were required to edit the README.md file which contains some information about the purpose of the repo.

Part B

For part B were required to create a meme using R using the following functions
- use of pipes e.g.%>%
- use of named objects e.g.meme <- image_read(url)
- use of comments e.g.# note to self
- use of indenting and white space

Part C

For part C we were required to create an animated gif using the following functions
- use of at least the {r} image_animate() function
- creation of at least 4 different frames for the animation using a combination of different functions from the {magick} package
- use of named objects e.g.{r} meme <- image_read(url)
- use of comments e.g.{r} # note to self
- use of indenting and white space

Part D

Part D was creating the html file which contained our meme, gif, descriptions for both and showing our knowledge and creativity of R, html and css by customizing our web page.

Part E

The final part of the practical aspect of this project was uploading the files to my github repository and finalising the website to display all my masterpieces which I have created (the meme and gif)


Learning Reflection



From this project I was able to reinforce my knowledge in R and my ability to code and think logically as I have little experience in coding. Although my coding knowledge is mostly python, I was able to put to transfer the logic and coding conventions to R and use them in my project. The most important idea I learnt was to think logically, by tracing my code to know exactly what everything does and how it runs so I am able to fix any bugs that arise (I did have a few bugs which put me at a halt a few times during this project).

Im curious to explore further what R has to offer such as what it can do with data and displaying it, being able to visualize and communicate the data and knowing what it all means. I am also looking forward to being able to increase my skill in coding with R and my skill in thinking logically.
